        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 62:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The meaning here is, that the psalmist felt assured that God would give him prosperity, as if his lamp were kept constantly burning in his dwelling.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The Lord my God will enlighten my darkness - Will shed light on my path, which would otherwise be dark: will impart light to my understanding; will put peace and joy in my heart; will crown me with his favor. Compare the note at Psalm 4:6. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "The Lord my God will enlighten my darkness - Will shed light on my path, which would otherwise be dark: will impart light to my understanding; will put peace and joy in my heart; will crown me with his favor. Compare the note at ",
            "children": []
